'''The [[beat|Beat]] [[generation|Generation]]'''

# A group of American [[writer]]s who came to prominence in the late 1950s and early 1960s. Their most important works are Jack Kerouac's On the Road (1957), Allen Ginsberg's Howl (1956), and William S. Burroughs' Naked Lunch (1959).